Apple unifies visual media with one tokenizer

<break time="1s" />
Apple released research on AToken this week, a multimodal architecture that uses a single encoder and tokenizer to handle images, video, and three-dimensional objects. Multimodal models typically use different tokenizers for different media types and different encoders when training to generate media rather than classify it. AToken consolidates that architecture into a single unified pipeline, which Apple argues simplifies training and reduces the overhead of maintaining separate encoding systems for each media type. The research signals the direction Apple is taking as it builds out its own AI infrastructure underneath products announced for later in 2026.

