World Impact

<break time="1s" />
Seoul ECG platform wins inaugural cardiology AI award

<break time="1s" />
Medical AI, a Seoul-based company specializing in AI-enabled electrocardiogram solutions for cardiovascular disease detection, received the inaugural Global Digital Health Award at the American College of Cardiology's Annual Scientific Session on March 29. The award recognizes organizations outside the United States that are demonstrating measurable real-world impact through digital health innovation.

<break time="1s" />

The company's platform analyzes raw data from standard twelve-lead electrocardiograms, enabling clinicians to detect multiple cardiovascular conditions earlier and more accurately, including heart failure, myocardial infarction, and aortic stenosis. The technology is supported by more than seventy indexed clinical publications and has received regulatory approvals in six countries, including CE marking, with FDA clearance expected later in 2026.

